{"abstract":[{"text":"Update your AppKit app to take full advantage of the new design system. We’ll dive into key changes to tab views, split views, bars, presentations, search, and controls, and show you how to use Liquid Glass in your custom UI. To get the most out of this video, we recommend first watching “Get to know the new design system” for general design guidance.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":2,"text":"Key Takeaways","anchor":"Key-Takeaways","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The new design provides refreshed materials and controls throughout macOS."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Windows and controls have new metrics, with escape hatches for compatibility."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The Liquid Glass material can be adopted by custom views as well as system controls.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":2,"text":"App structure","anchor":"App-structure","type":"heading"},{"level":3,"text":"Windows","anchor":"Windows","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Window shape has been altered.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Key structural regions, like sidebar and toolbar, are framed in glass.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Windows have a larger corner radius."}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"identifier":"WWDC25-310-Window-Corner-Radius","type":"image"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":3,"text":"Avoiding window corners","anchor":"Avoiding-window-corners","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use new ","type":"text"},{"code":"NSView.LayoutRegion","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" to obtain a layout guide avoiding a corner.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unordered